{"children":[{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/51d182b2d63641759645005d05c8561f","type":"heading","createdTime":1593672692000,"lastEditedTime":1593672660000,"title":[["Nalanda University VR"]],"depth":1},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/8b2bf2d7191b4c2081c5919b5c649d50","type":"text","createdTime":1593672660000,"lastEditedTime":1593672840000,"title":[["Founded in the fifth century, Nalanda at its peak attracted some 10,000 students from all over the world to study Buddhism, law, literature, philosophy and science. It is said to have been the first global institution of higher learning — and, Indians note, one created long before the development of universities in Europe."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/5eee276e67b64e09a3d7f72be479beaa","type":"text","createdTime":1593672840000,"lastEditedTime":1593673500000,"title":[["My idea is to put together the Nalanda university as it existed in it's glorious days in VR and create an environment for students to study in World's most ancient and advanced university."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/525da32bcbd346c4912bc13aab638562","type":"text","createdTime":1593675840000,"lastEditedTime":1593675840000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/4d44336282634aada44e22f79074c9f4","type":"heading","createdTime":1593675882215,"lastEditedTime":1593675840000,"title":[["Presentation"]],"depth":3},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/5008a11dc6e34fd59537ffd91c493952","type":"file","createdTime":1593675888669,"lastEditedTime":1593675900000,"fileId":"eb4f0f8a-16bd-495b-8c29-ba057a3c408f","title":"Nalanda VR Presentation.pdf","size":"653.9KB","source":"https://www.notion.so/signed/https%3A%2F%2Fs3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2Fsecure.notion-static.com%2Feb4f0f8a-16bd-495b-8c29-ba057a3c408f%2FNalanda_VR_Presentation.pdf"},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/57260b88320b4b5fa21c6f5b55184f8f","type":"heading","createdTime":1593672738129,"lastEditedTime":1593672720000,"title":[["Brief"]],"depth":3},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/686b1c879ea1432a9f6c1b6f5ee5897f","type":"text","createdTime":1593672660000,"lastEditedTime":1593673560000,"title":[["A virtual classroom built in a VR environment which will simulate the Nalanda Mahavihara campus as it existed in the 5th century. The environment will be built after researching through all the public documents and ancient scriptures containing descriptions of the layout. "]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/8aaf360f991f46a294334b973d6898b2","type":"text","createdTime":1593675360000,"lastEditedTime":1593675420000,"title":[["Teaching methodology of the university is said to be very similar to gurukul teachings of sanatana dharma "],["https://www.sanatan.org/mr/a/14744.html",[["a","https://www.sanatan.org/mr/a/14744.html"]]]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/d454f1fe9f814b01b05fbec7842716be","type":"image","createdTime":1593675420000,"lastEditedTime":1593675420000,"source":"https://www.sanatan.org/mr/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2016/07/guru_shishya.jpg","caption":[],"width":-1,"height":-1,"fullWidth":false,"pageWidth":true,"aspectRatio":-1,"preserveScale":true},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/a7409160f2b94a6fb8a11f5955c0a6c2","type":"text","createdTime":1593675420000,"lastEditedTime":1593675420000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/16654242a0134f3c82e3105dbdc3660c","type":"text","createdTime":1593673080000,"lastEditedTime":1593675420000,"title":[["According to information made public by the Achaeological Survey of India, the campus had"]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/599c62e921914045b45f1adc5c147f7e","type":"text","createdTime":1593673140000,"lastEditedTime":1593673680000,"title":[["11 bauddha viharas (residential and educational buildings)"]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/990eb12ec2e5401e988e0cc5c9afc9d6","type":"text","createdTime":1593673200000,"lastEditedTime":1593673200000,"title":[["6 temples"]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/f07a8c3208c143f586c3314ad1b96369","type":"text","createdTime":1593673680000,"lastEditedTime":1593673680000,"title":[["stupas and shrines"]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/06cd5cdfce9645a1ba6ec2be32dc035f","type":"text","createdTime":1593673260000,"lastEditedTime":1593673620000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/8e8f7d0e776c4b7f832b21a49ec5cb76","type":"text","createdTime":1593673260000,"lastEditedTime":1593673620000,"title":[["Virtual walk through of the Nalanda campus is available Google Images "]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/795a4d3db1b44058a6ce43a0f3305ed7","type":"text","createdTime":1593673620000,"lastEditedTime":1593673620000,"title":[["https://artsandculture.google.com/exhibit/nalanda- from-mound-to-monument-archaeological-survey-of-india/gQrWSylT?hl=en",[["a","https://artsandculture.google.com/exhibit/nalanda-%C2%A0from-mound-to-monument-archaeological-survey-of-india/gQrWSylT?hl=en"]]]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/5f93c69260794f9bb0891bef0a6c136b","type":"text","createdTime":1593675180000,"lastEditedTime":1593675180000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/3412994ececc4ce9b8db6b62a858a268","type":"text","createdTime":1593675120000,"lastEditedTime":1593675420000,"title":[["Architectural Plam of the NALANDA MAHAVIHARA"]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/800e3002259f4ddbb6b5e088c2ec7f73","type":"image","createdTime":1593675181922,"lastEditedTime":1593675180000,"source":"http://www.kamit.jp/02_unesco/26_nalanda/plan_na2.jpg","caption":[],"width":-1,"height":-1,"fullWidth":false,"pageWidth":true,"aspectRatio":-1,"preserveScale":true},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/cfdd75225bd7415a8f78d38d01cea613","type":"text","createdTime":1593675240000,"lastEditedTime":1593675240000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/3106b7d0b65b465dbb2f53b796f68c65","type":"image","createdTime":1593675249648,"lastEditedTime":1593675240000,"source":"https://www.photodharma.net/India/Nalanda/Cunninghams-Drawing.jpg","caption":[],"width":-1,"height":-1,"fullWidth":false,"pageWidth":true,"aspectRatio":-1,"preserveScale":true},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/ddba520c93ae44109c3a1819cae12198","type":"heading","createdTime":1593672743390,"lastEditedTime":1593672720000,"title":[["Slides"]],"depth":3},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/a76c5b7624d54e34859b0b6edba570d8","type":"text","createdTime":1593672660000,"lastEditedTime":1593672660000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/e9a494bfe38d49b698fb4538815f5e3c","type":"text","createdTime":1593672749845,"lastEditedTime":1593675360000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/f68005eb62584d088850a240a39751e6","type":"heading","createdTime":1593673735157,"lastEditedTime":1593673680000,"title":[["History"]],"depth":3},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/e1eb3f7aa8bd48479a764a0e21c729f1","type":"text","createdTime":1593673680000,"lastEditedTime":1593673680000,"title":[["The Nalanda Mahavihara site is in the State of Bihar, in north-eastern India. It comprises the archaeological remains of a monastic and scholastic institution dating from the 3rd century BCE to the 13th century CE. It includes stupas, shrines, viharas (residential and educational buildings) and important art works in stucco, stone and metal. Nalanda stands out as the most ancient university of the Indian Subcontinent. It engaged in the organized transmission of knowledge over an uninterrupted period of 800 years. The historical development of the site testifies to the development of Buddhism into a religion and the flourishing of monastic and educational traditions."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/9afe3682dc964346a565882579afdcb9","type":"text","createdTime":1593673800000,"lastEditedTime":1593673800000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/f9e22a6e0cd649e5b567c5cc2c666669","type":"text","createdTime":1593673834095,"lastEditedTime":1593673800000,"title":[["Nalanda Mahavihara, as a centre for higher learning marks the zenith in the evolution of sangharama (monastic establishment) into the earliest higher learning establishment of early medieval India. Its merit-based approach said to have embraced all contemporary sources of knowledge and systems of learning practiced in the Indian subcontinent."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/bba5807c068b45509484e76818782907","type":"text","createdTime":1593673834096,"lastEditedTime":1593673800000,"title":[["Nalanda remains one of the earliest and longest serving extraordinary institution-builder. Its systems of pedagogy, administration, planning and architecture were the basis on which later Mahaviharas were established. Nalanda continues to inspire modern university establishments in the region like Nava Nalanda Mahavihara, Nalanda University and several others across Asia."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/f34e7496b2f54e2e98e1bf3eda01eaa0","type":"text","createdTime":1593672660000,"lastEditedTime":1593672660000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/fe497ddd7acc49d5816938eee1b73806","type":"bookmark","createdTime":1593672720000,"lastEditedTime":1593672720000,"link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nalanda_University","title":"Nalanda University","description":"Nalanda University (also known as Nalanda International University) is an international and research-intensive class located in the historical city of Rajgir, in Bihar, India. It was established by an Act of Parliament to emulate the famous ancient university of Nalanda, which functioned between the 5th and 13th centuries.","icon":"https://en.wikipedia.org/static/favicon/wikipedia.ico","cover":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d6/Nalanda_University_Logo.gif"},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/482e133b4d914238aab7bd0d14307615","type":"text","createdTime":1593673320000,"lastEditedTime":1593673320000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/6aaf2c4f5feb464a93d28947a850096c","type":"text","createdTime":1593673320000,"lastEditedTime":1593673320000,"title":[["The decline of Nalanda had come with the end of Pala dynasty. Turkish invasions came as a final blow for its destruction in 12th century. Despite of few attempts at resuscitation, this great centre of Buddhist learning fell into complete disrepair, and was inhabited by locals."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/9884a8de18c1498a86e3dfb6a5a36d2f","type":"text","createdTime":1593673320000,"lastEditedTime":1593673320000,"title":[["Sir Alexander Cunningham, the founder of the Archaeological Survey of India, surveyed and provided a complete description of the site in 1860s."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/75cf0d88c73740bd8747b563bef12352","type":"text","createdTime":1593673440000,"lastEditedTime":1593675360000,"title":[["Fa-Hien and Hsuan Tsang, the Chinese travelers, provide detailed descriptions of Nalanda Mahavihara."]]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/692edc6e080f4bc5925320d748b0f55d","type":"text","createdTime":1593673020000,"lastEditedTime":1593673020000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/7a2c213d92594169bbdce0291a71a08f","type":"text","createdTime":1593673020000,"lastEditedTime":1593673020000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/d54ee683983842b3aec74b37db82a24a","type":"text","createdTime":1593673020000,"lastEditedTime":1593673020000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/10a2842247864286aad08d8239827671","type":"heading","createdTime":1593673060157,"lastEditedTime":1593673020000,"title":[["Research"]],"depth":3},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/72834ff9b2b04030859fa262493d278a","type":"text","createdTime":1593673020000,"lastEditedTime":1593673020000,"title":[["DD TV report "],["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nfq5W3qw48E",[["a","https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nfq5W