ssal, red-brick ruins of Nalanda University at the age of 11. After he told his family that he wanted to be a professor, his grandfather took him to see the remains of what is described as India's oldest university, a place where history has the cast of epic myth.","icon":"https://www.nytimes.com/vi-assets/static-assets/favicon-4bf96cb6a1093748bf5b3c429accb9b4.ico","cover":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/03/24/education/24iht-educlede24-top/24iht-educlede24-top-articleLarge.jpg"},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/196d436038e147c98623921c225f4d91","type":"text","createdTime":1593675120000,"lastEditedTime":1593675120000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/7195e34604e44b568137ab19c19eaf00","type":"bookmark","createdTime":1593675120000,"lastEditedTime":1593675120000,"link":"http://www.kamit.jp/02_unesco/26_nalanda/xplan_naeng.htm","title":"PLAN of the NALANDA MAHAVIHARA (Buddhist University)","description":"PLAN of the NALANDA MAHAVIHARA (Buddhist University)","cover":"http://www.kamit.jp/02_unesco/26_nalanda/plan_na2.jpg"},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/fa037d1ae2514589802a79b1af087ffd","type":"text","createdTime":1593675240000,"lastEditedTime":1593675240000,"title":[]},{"children":[],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/16f06cfdea8142e6b6d8353b25e67543","type":"bookmark","createdTime":1593675240000,"lastEditedTime":1593675240000,"link":"https://www.photodharma.net/India/Nalanda/History-of-Nalanda.htm","title":"Short History of Nalanda","description":"Short History of Nālanda Text adapted from a sign in the Archeological Park The history of Nālanda goes back to the days of Mahāvīra and the Buddha in the 6th century B.C. It was where Sāriputta, one of the Chief Disciples of the Buddha was born and passed into Nibbāna.","cover":"https://www.photodharma.net/India/Nalanda/Cunninghams-Drawing.jpg"}],"uri":"https://www.notion.so/05158fa84ec44872afb2959678cae332","type":"page","createdTime":1593672600000,"lastEditedTime":1593675900000,